Camel pose is one of my favorite heart-opening yoga poses. Back when I had suffered a devastating loss, I went to a yoga class and kept falling out of the camel pose because it was too intense and made me feel an explosion of emotion. I kept trying to come back in to the pose but would fall right back out. After class, the yoga instructor pulled me aside and asked if I was ok because typically when someone is going through a lot emotionally, this pose can be challenging. I was shocked. It’s interesting how our minds and bodies are so connected.

My goal this summer: Be the softest, most lathered up, best smelling luxurious goddess summer fairy. 🤷🏻‍♀️

ULTA HAUL! Let me show you what I added to my Summer 2023 Goddess Summer Fairy product collection. 

1. My summer 2023 signature scent- Daisy Dream by Marc Jacobs.

Originally I overlooked this perfume because I assumed it would be basic. I was looking online for perfumes that contain pear notes, (I LOVE pear notes in perfume), and I stumbled across Daisy Dream by Marc Jacobs. I fell in love when I read the rest of the notes, too!

Notes:
Top: Blackberry, grapefruit, pear 
Heart: Jasmine, lychee, blue wisteria 
Base: White woods, musks, coconut water 

2. “Hydrate Ever After” by Sweetspot. It’s a daily moisturizer for your 🐱 !!!! I didn’t even know that was a thing until I ran across this in Ulta! I decided it’s the best “extra” self-care, pampering product I must have. 

3. Coco Cloud Whipped Shave Butter by Truly. 
It’s poofy. It’s soft. It’s cloud-like. It’s wonderful. Makes my legs so soft. 

4. Glazed Doughnut After Shave Oil by Truly.
This stuff smells like actual doughnuts and it’s PURPLE oil. Hands down my top fav item out of all of these. Also makes my legs super soft. 

5. Vegan Collagen Booster by Truly. 
It looks good enough to eat. Packed with vitamin C and contains retinol. You wear it overnight 2-3 times a week and I woke up to bouncy, plump, hydrated skin!

What I bring in my bag for yachting.
It’s usually a long day with lots of people. I like to pack a bag for when I take a breather in the back room and hit the refresh button. I forgot to add in this video that I almost always pack a bottle of water and electrolytes! 

1. Alba Botanicals Day-To-Day Setting Mist SPF 30- This is the ONLY facial sunscreen I’ve ever liked. It works well under or over makeup, is lightweight and non-greasy. 

2. Coola Classic Sunscreen Spray- My favorite body sunscreen because it’s non-greasy and goes on clear. 

3. Hand Sanitizer- Just because germs and lots of people. 

4. Diff Eyewear shades in “KOKO” gradient- My favorite pair of sunglasses I own. 

5. Anastasia Shimmer Body Oil- This is sparkly and gives goddess vibes. ✨

6. Perfume “Daisy Dream” by Marc Jacobs- A delicious scent I recently discovered that is fruity and juicy. 

7. Rhode Peptide Lip Treatment in “Passionfruit Jelly”- I’m weirdly obsessed with this stuff. I wear it daily and put it on before bed to wake up to plump, soft lips. I bring it everywhere.

8. Hair Clip- Because hair up is always comfy and it gets hot! 

9. Eye Drops- I’m not a smoker, eye drops just do something for me. 😂 They make me feel so refreshed and revitalized. I love bringing them boating. 

10. Buxom Lipgloss in “Sarina”- This is a browny-pink sparkly plumping gloss that I like for summer.

What’s better than staying out late partying? 
Waking up early and doing yoga in the sunshine
Going for a morning run on the beach
Traveling while completely sober so you don’t forget a single moment or dull your senses to experience it all
Dancing in the daylight with your best friends
Riding horses on the countryside 
Zip lining through the forest 

What’s better than casual hookups? 
Deep, meaningful relationships 
Passionate, hot nights with strong connection 
Being intimate with someone you know always has your back 
Love
Family 

Sometimes I think people lose sight of what’s out there for them and chase temporary highs in attempt to fulfill deep needs and desires. 

To me, life is so much richer and delicious while sober and when I have meaningful relationships.

Things I’ve learned about friendship and people over time:

1. Protect your energy at all costs.

2. The best revenge is simply cutting off their access to you. 

3. When you’re being your authentic self- you’ll attract people who love you for your authentic self.

4. There are people who will make you realize you’re easy to love, and who see the good in you. 

5. Your gut instinct is usually right. 

6. Allow yourself to be lonely until you find genuine, loving people.

7. An insecure person is a dangerous person. 

8. People’s success should inspire you, not upset you. Surround yourself with people who get inspired- and be one of them. 

9. Pour the love you wish to receive in to others. 

10. Don’t always wait for people to reach out to you. Be the first to send that text or initiate plans. 

11. Being a good friend isn’t hard. People who act like it is aren’t your people.

When I’m stressed, I like to indulge all the senses at once to bring me back to the present moment and regulate my nervous system. 

Touch- Massage, a hot shower, bath, etc. This is probably the biggest one for me, personally. Physical touch is like medicine to me!

Sight- Clean up your space, de-clutter, look at a beautiful painting or imagery, look at photos that make you happy, put a vase of your favorite flowers out where you can see them. 

Smell- light a candle, put on your favorite perfume, start your essential oil diffuser. 

Taste- make a healthy mocktail or a healthy snack. 

Sound- listen to something you love such as music or white noise. 

I set up this environment for myself and then engage in an activity like art or meditation. It works every time.
